锘縶"ok":true,"query":"Explain Surah Al-Baqarah with tafsir","route_type":"explicit_quran_reference","action_type":"explain","route":{"route_type":"explicit_quran_reference","action_type":"explain","confidence":0.98,"signals":["surah_reference_name","explain_language","tafsir_intent"],"secondary_intents":["tafsir_request"],"reason":"explicit_quran_reference_detected","normalized_query":"surah al-baqarah with","parsed_reference":{"surah_no":2,"ayah_start":null,"ayah_end":null,"parse_type":"surah_name_with_optional_ayah"},"reference_text":"surah al-baqarah","reference_match_type":"surah_reference_name","query_normalization":{"raw_query":"Explain Surah Al-Baqarah with tafsir","normalized_query":"Explain Surah Al-Baqarah with tafsir","backend":"openai","changed":false,"confidence":1.0,"normalization_type":"identity","did_change_meaning":false,"safe_for_routing":true,"used_hosted_model":true,"attempted_hosted_model":true,"model":"gpt-4o-mini","hosted_model":"gpt-4o-mini"}},"answer_mode":"quran_with_tafsir","terminal_state":"answered","answer_text":"Quran 2:1-286 says: Alif. Lam. Mim. This is the Book of Allah: there is no doubt about it. It is guidance to God-fearing people, who believe in the unseen, establish the Salats, and expend (in Our way) out of what We have bestowed on them. Those who believe in the Book We have sent down to you (i.e. the Qur'an) and in the Books sent down before you, and firmly believe in the Hereafter芒聙聰such people are on the right way from their Lord and such are truly successful. As for those who have rejected (these things), it is all the same to them whether you warn them or do not warn them: they are not going to believe. Allah has sealed up their hearts and ears, and a covering has fallen over their eyes; they have incurred the severest punishment. \n\nTafsir Ibn Kathir emphasizes that these verses highlight the undeniable truth of the Qur'an and its role as divine guidance. Imam Abu Ja`far bin Jarir explains that Allah has sent clear signs that testify to the prophethood of Muhammad.  \n\nMa'arif al-Qur'an highlights the plight of hypocrites through similes: those deeply rooted in disbelief pretend to be believers for worldly motives, while others, who recognize the truth, struggle with doubts. \n\nTafheem al-Qur'an states that the letters \"Alif, Lam, Mim\" are part of the literary tradition known as huruf muqatta'at and were commonly understood by the Arabs at the time of revelation. These letters don't affect the reader's ability to find guidance in the Qur'an.","citations":[{"source_id":"quran:tanzil-simple","citation_text":"Quran 2:1-286","canonical_ref":"quran:2:1-286","source_domain":"quran"},{"source_id":"tafsir:ibn-kathir-en","citation_text":"Tafsir Ibn Kathir on Quran 2:99-103","canonical_ref":"tafsir:ibn-kathir-en:82710","source_domain":"tafsir"},{"source_id":"tafsir:ibn-kathir-en","citation_text":"Tafsir Ibn Kathir on Quran 2:68-71","canonical_ref":"tafsir:ibn-kathir-en:82693","source_domain":"tafsir"},{"source_id":"tafsir:ibn-kathir-en","citation_text":"Tafsir Ibn Kathir on Quran 2:159-162","canonical_ref":"tafsir:ibn-kathir-en:82743","source_domain":"tafsir"},{"source_id":"tafsir:maarif-al-quran-en","citation_text":"Ma'arif al-Qur'an on Quran 2:17-20","canonical_ref":"tafsir:maarif-al-quran-en:79625","source_domain":"tafsir"},{"source_id":"tafsir:maarif-al-quran-en","citation_text":"Ma'arif al-Qur'an on Quran 2:68-71","canonical_ref":"tafsir:maarif-al-quran-en:79665","source_domain":"tafsir"},{"source_id":"tafsir:maarif-al-quran-en","citation_text":"Ma'arif al-Qur'an on Quran 2:204-207","canonical_ref":"tafsir:maarif-al-quran-en:79765","source_domain":"tafsir"},{"source_id":"tafsir:tafheem-al-quran-en","citation_text":"Tafheem al-Quran on Quran 2:1","canonical_ref":"tafsir:tafheem-al-quran-en:2:1","source_domain":"tafsir"},{"source_id":"tafsir:tafheem-al-quran-en","citation_text":"Tafheem al-Quran on Quran 2:2","canonical_ref":"tafsir:tafheem-al-quran-en:2:2","source_domain":"tafsir"},